{
  "texts": [
    "This led to exploding gradients, returning all zeroes as the output.",
    "To solve this issue, we gradually increased the complexity of the task by subsampling the data and transforming the distribution of area density.",
    "The process is commonly known as curriculum learning (Wang et al., 2021), which lets the model learn a simple task at the start, and the process continues by gradually increasing the complexity of the subsequent tasks, each one linked to the previous one.",
    "To do so, we first removed all data points that contained zeros among the area density 1 km grids.",
    "We then log-transformed the target variable to convert the exponential-like distribution to a Gaussian-like distribution."
  ]
}